ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.116                Enzyme
NAME        3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA dehydratase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA hydro-lyase
REACTION    3-hydroxypropanoyl-CoA = acryloyl-CoA + H2O [RN:R03045]
ALL_REAC    R03045
SUBSTRATE   3-hydroxypropanoyl-CoA [CPD:C05668]
PRODUCT     acryloyl-CoA [CPD:C00894];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     Catalyses a step in the 3-hydroxypropionate/4-hydroxybutyrate cycle, an autotrophic CO2 fixation pathway found in some thermoacidophilic archaea [1]. The enzyme from Metallosphaera sedula acts nearly equally as well on (S)-3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA but not (R)-3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA [2].
